<section xml:id="sect-intro-exp">
<title>Exponential and Logarithmic functions</title>

		<p>
			After introducing the linear functions, power functions, and polynomial functions, we can address exponential and logarithmic functions. These two panic-inducing functions are probably among the most used in calculations in the lab sciences. Consider the following curve.
		</p>
<p>INSERT GRAPH</p>
		<p>
			We can contrast the form of power functions and exponential functions and try to build some intuition.
		</p>

		<p>
			Which of the following are exponential functions?
		</p>

		<p><ul>	<li><p><m>f(x) = x^2</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>f(x) = e^x</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>f(x) = 10^x</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>f(x) = x^e</m></p></li>

		</ul></p>

		<p>
			Also helpful are the following rules that work for real numbers <m>a, n, m</m>.
		</p>

		<p><ul>	<li><p><m>a^n\cdot a^m =</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>(a^n)^m =</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>a^{-m} =</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>\dfrac{a^n}{a^m} =</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>a^0 =</m></p></li>
	<li><p><m>a^1 =</m></p></li>

		</ul></p>

		<p>
			These rules also work when the base is a variable like <m>x</m> or the base of an exponential function like <m>e</m>. Likewise we can have expressions involving variables in exponents.
		</p>

		<p>
			<em>Caution:</em> We do not have rules for things like <m>a^m + a^n</m> (or, assuming <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are different, <m>a^n\cdot b^m</m>).
		</p>

		<p>
			Before getting into too many problems that use exponentials, we should review the logarithm - it is necessary for <em>some, but not all</em> problems involving exponentials. (See separate page.)
		</p>

		<p>
			These functions are inverses, so <me>e^{\ln(x)} = x \text{ and } \ln(e^x) = x.</me> This is helpful for solving equations involving exponential functions.
		</p>

		<p>
			Before getting to that, what are logarithms? Logarithms often show up when we need to systematically (and reversibly) manipulate formulas or data. For example, we can use the base-10 logarithm below, as we might in a spreadsheet.
