			What just happened?
		</p>

		<p>
			To introduce the logarithm as the inverse function to an exponential function, it is helpful to think of powers of ten. Consider how we express large numbers in scientific notation, <me>1,000,000 = 10^6</me> To write one million, we multiply  factors of . We say,
